						               													<description>(from the manual :)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Napoleon Returns is a Volley &amp;amp; Bayonet scenario book covering history's most famous campaign. It provides:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- historical background on the four battles of Quatre Bras, Ligny, Waterloo &amp;amp; Wavre.&amp;#10;- complete scenarios for all four battles.&amp;#10;- a Campaign System which allows you to re-fight history's most famous campaign.&amp;#10;- a rules update to refine Volley &amp;amp; Bayonet for Napoleonic Warfare.&amp;#10;- an extensive look at all the armies and their uniforms.&amp;#10;- a complete order of battle, and labels for unit bases to allow quick set-up.&amp;#10;- a point system to allow you to design you own scenarios.&amp;#10;- 9 maps, one each for the terrain and deployment for each battle, and a 2 page campaign map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Volley &amp; Bayonet is the most practical way to fight the great campaigns of 1815. Find out if Napoleon has to meet another Waterloo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
